            <h2>Debian KDE Team Web Maintenance<img alt="webmaint_icon" src="../images/webmaint_64.png" style="float:right; margin:-8px 0 0 0;" /></h2>

            The webpage code is kept in <a href="http://anonscm.debian.org/gitweb/?p=pkg-kde/www.git;a=summary">this GIT repo</a>.<br/>
            Steps to modify it:<br/>
            <br/>

            <ol>
               <li>Edit/create pages (without .html suffix) in folder './pages/'.<br />
                   These pages must only include its very own content.<br />
                   Header, sidebar and footer are in files 'top' and 'bottom' and will be appended <br />
		   by running genweb.sh script in the next step.</li>

               <li>Run script './genweb.sh'. It will create full-fledged pages in folder './output/'.</li>

               <li>Use a browser to check your changes, and repeat previous steps if necessary.</li>

               <li>Commit the modifications you did inside 'pages/'.</li>

	       <li>For publishing the changes, run genweb.sh from the git repository root and copy
		   the content from output to moszumanska:/home/groups/pkg-kde/htdocs/.</li>
            </ol>
